{"type":"message","id":"943047e7","parentId":"37f4c830","timestamp":"2026-04-12T02:31:23.997Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Sam is saying Rebecca is an \"agent\" (sub-agent) and he doesn't know her ID, and he wants me to fix it.\n\nSo Rebecca is a sub-agent running in OpenClaw, not a Telegram user. The \"Rebecca_lookitrybot\" chat is supposed to be between the bot and Rebecca (the sub-agent), but somehow Sam's messages are coming through to me instead.\n\nWait, I think I understand now. Let me re-read...\n\nThe bot `@Rebecca_lookitrybot` was created for Rebecca to chat with Sammy. But somehow Sam's messages (from his Telegram account) are reaching me here. This might be because the bot is configured with Sam's ID as an authorized sender instead of Rebecca's.\n\n\nThe real issue is that this Telegram bot is probably connected to OpenClaw and mapped to the `sammy` agent, but the authorized senders are set to Sam's Telegram ID instead of Rebecca's sub-agent identity. I need to check the OpenClaw config to see what IDs are configured for authorized senders, since Rebecca is a sub-agent and might have her own identifier within the system rather than a Telegram user ID.","thinkingSignature":"48528d2173be9770e7667c87b3f6ae195ad0a689021aade6dd8fd90b7f542e73"},{"type":"text","text":"Ah, Rebecca es un **sub-agente**, no un usuario de Telegram. Entendido.\n\nDéjame revisar la configuración actual de OpenClaw para ver cómo está mapeado el bot y los authorized senders.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1y7zd3kmtpr7_1","name":"gateway","arguments":{"action":"config.get"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":107,"output":308,"cacheRead":22873,"cacheWrite":42,"totalTokens":23330,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775961073546,"responseId":"062a36f175d5aad1632004d99a2ac2d2"}}
